Dear List,

Is there any rule of thumb on how many independent observation are 
necessary for fitting distribution mixture with n parameters to get 
reliable parameter estimates? I'm aware that observations should be more 
than parameters, but near to this minimum the estimations become 
unreliable (standard errors will be high).? I'm also aware that for an 
actual data set I can decide the optimal complexity calculating BIC. 
What I would need is a guess on how decision on sample size will 
constrain the possible complexity of fitted model. I would use it in a 
publication, so a reference that I could cite is warmly welcome.

Thanks

Zoltan


